        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### What SRD-46 covers\n\nSRD-46 is focused on **small-molecule ligands** and their equilibrium stability constants with metal ions. The ligand classes in the database include:\n\n| Ligand class | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Amino Acids | 297 |\n| Peptides | 157 |\n| Polypeptides | 98 |\n| Tripeptides | 66 |\n| Aliphatic amines | 250 |\n| Pyridines | 248 |\n| Carboxylic acids | 182 |\n| EDTA and derivatives | 115 |\n| … and ~50 more small-molecule classes | |\n\nThe closest entries to biological macromolecules are **amino acids**, **peptides**, **tripeptides**, and **polypeptides** — but these are small, well-defined molecules (e.g., glycine, glutathione, short oligopeptides), not intact proteins.",
