      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Why proteins aren't included\n\nStability constants in the thermodynamic sense (log β, log K) are well-defined for metal–small-ligand equilibria in solution. For proteins like transferrin, the binding is far more complex — involving multiple binding sites, conformational changes, and kinetic factors — and is typically characterized by **binding affinities (Kd)** or **association constants** measured by specialized biophysical techniques (ITC, SPR, fluorescence quenching) rather than classical potentiometric/spectrophotometric methods used for SRD-46 data.",
